  "text": "Male frogs weighed an average 2.2 ± 0.7 g and had a mean SVL of 25.6 ± 0.3 mm (mean ± standard deviation). As expected, female frogs were bigger than male frogs weighing an average 2.8 ± 0.6 g and had a mean SVL of 28.8 ± 0.2 mm. No association was found between sex of the frog and infection status (MannWhitney U = 250, P = 0.848, n = 72). Additionally, size and weight of frogs were not significantly correlated with Bd intensity (size; ρ = 0.130, P = 0.278, n = 72; weight; ρ = −0.082, P = 0.496, n = 72). No clinical signs of chytridiomycosis were observed in any of the frogs surveyed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
